
[1]insinuation

   INSINUA'TION, n. [L. insinuatio.]

   1. The act of insinuating; a creeping or winding in; a flowing into
   crevices.

   2. The act of gaining on favor or affections, by gentle or artful
   means.

   3. The art or power of pleasing and stealing on the affections.

   He had a natural insinuation and address; which made him acceptable in
   the best company.

   4. A hint; a suggestion or intimation by distant allusion. Slander may
   be conveyed by insinuation.
